ac0f7b07-7e2d-5db5-9019-75d7cb7c44f0,tg:rubgr:2746,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"[6 bladen] [blad 1, recto] Colour. Naples: grey-bluish tonality with subdued green. In the centre a few red spots different colouristic treatment of the sails; Icarus: nearest to it: in the bluish tonality which receives a pinkish fringe in the centre the one strong red accent in sleeve and collar of ploughman. There are a few delicate red [...] the roofs and the flag of the ship [...]; [blad 1, verso] 1559/60 Proverbs: similar to Carnival & Lent, but here the blue red centre motif stressed more strongly and repeated more often in the picture [...]; [blad 2, recto] Colour. 1562 Dulle Griet extremely bold: Here the ground in which everything is imbedded is brown and red and here the central figure combines these in her sleeve [...]; [blad 2, verso] 1562 Monkeys. Berlin. Almost monochrome, but very delicat contrast between brownish tone and grey blue (background). Ground by the brown-grey chain, reddish accents in hair of monkeys & heads [...]; [blad 3, recto] Colour. 1564 Way to Calvary. The basic grounds are here - but the spring green has become extremely strong and the rest is arranged in a regular pattern [...]; [blad 3, verso] but also by distinction between brown and reddish brick (entwined by white and reddish vertical ships of shore) [...]; [blad 4, recto] Colour. 1565 Months [...]; [blad 4, verso] 1566 Census at Bethlehem [...]; [blad 5, recto] Colour. 1567 Adoration Reinhardt [...]; [blad 5, verso] 1568 Faithlessness of World [...]; [blad 6, recto] Colour. 1568 The Blind [...]; [blad 6, verso] Wedding Meal] [scan]",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>[6 bladen] [blad 1, recto] Colour. Naples: grey-bluish tonality with subdued green. In the centre a few red spots different colouristic treatment of the sails; Icarus: nearest to it: in the bluish tonality which receives a pinkish fringe in the centre the one strong red accent in sleeve and collar of ploughman. Berlin. Almost monochrome, but very delicat contrast between brownish tone and grey blue (background). Ground by the brown-grey chain, reddish accents in hair of monkeys & heads [...]; [blad 3, recto] Colour. 1564 Way to Calvary. The basic grounds are here - but the spring green has become extremely strong and the rest is arranged in a regular pattern [...]; [blad 3, verso] but also by distinction between brown and reddish brick (entwined by white and reddish vertical ships of shore) [...]; [blad 4, recto] Colour. 1565 Months [...]; [blad 4, verso] 1566 Census at Bethlehem [...]; [blad 5, recto] Colour. 1567 Adoration Reinhardt [...]; [blad 5, verso] 1568 Faithlessness of World [...]; [blad 6, recto] Colour. 1568 The Blind [...]; [blad 6, verso] Wedding Meal] [scan]</content>
